{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pullrequests/181/comments/110170260.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/diff/mingfeisun/ign-rendering:c2585318b499..97b6d5a83955?path=ogre%2Fsrc%2FOgreMesh.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pull-requests/181/_/diff#comment-110170260"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 181, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pullrequests/181.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pull-requests/181"}}, "title": "Add support for playing Actor animation"}, "content": {"raw": "It's fine to keep this as is, but I ([and many other people](https://softwareengineering.stackexchange.com/questions/18454/should-i-return-from-a-function-early-or-use-an-if-statement)) usually recommend returning early to make the code easier to read. \n\nSo here you could do\n\n```\nif (!this->ogreEntity->hasSkeleton())\n  return;\n```\n\nand \n\n```\nif (!skel->hasBone(pair.first))\n  continue;\n```", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>It's fine to keep this as is, but I (<a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://softwareengineering.stackexchange.com/questions/18454/should-i-return-from-a-function-early-or-use-an-if-statement\" rel=\"nofollow\">and many other people</a>) usually recommend returning early to make the code easier to read. </p>\n<p>So here you could do</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>if (!this-&gt;ogreEntity-&gt;hasSkeleton())\n  return;\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>and </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>if (!skel-&gt;hasBone(pair.first))\n  continue;\n</pre></div>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-07-22T14:45:59.389396+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-b